SUMMARY:Mindfulness in the Garden (Weekday Series)
DESCRIPTION:Mindfulness in the Garden (Weekday Series) \nInstructor: Jodi Brooks \nTuesdays\, 11:00 AM – 12:00 PM \nEarly Spring Session: Apr 7\, 14\, & 28 (No class 4/21) \nDiscover how a mindfulness practice can help us awaken and live in harmony with oneself and with the natural world. This class will include: simple instructions for getting started with a formal mindfulness practice\, very gentle stretching & breathwork\, and an outdoor contemplative garden walk. This is a practice of slowing down\, cultivating quiet and paying attention to our senses. All levels are welcome. No experience needed. Spring classes will be held outdoors\, with a short walk (weather permitting). \nFee: 3 April classes: General public $75\, Members $60 \nShare this:\n				Share on Facebook (Opens in new window)\n				Facebook\n			\n				Share on Bluesky (Opens in new window)\n				Bluesky\n			\n				Share on LinkedIn (Opens in new window)\n				LinkedIn\n			\n				Share on Threads (Opens in new window)\n				Threads\n			\n				Share on Nextdoor (Opens in new window)\n				Nextdoor\n			\n				Share on WhatsApp (Opens in new window)\n				WhatsApp\n			\n				Email a link to a friend (Opens in new window)\n				Email
