SUMMARY:Open Book / Open Mind; Nicholas Lemann\, "Returning"
DESCRIPTION:Join Montclair Public Library for another amazing author conversation! Co-presented by Bnai Keshet\, Congregation Shomrei Emunah\, Temple Ner Tamid and Temple Sholom of West Essex. Register now at tinyurl.com/OBOMLemann \nNew Yorker staff writer Nicholas Lemann will talk to journalist and author Dale Russakoff (“The Prize”) about “Returning\,” his new memoir about 300 years of his Jewish family in Louisiana\, exploring their stories from peddlers to plantation owners (and enslavers) as well as merchants and professionals.\n“What does it mean to belong? ‘Returning’ offers a profound mediation on family\, Jewish identity\, and the meaning of home in a world constantly shaken by economic\, social\, and cultural change.”― Henry Louis Gates Jr.\nDoors open at 6 p.m. The discussion will be followed by an audience Q&A and book sales and signing with Watchung Booksellers. \nShare this:\n				Share on Facebook (Opens in new window)\n				Facebook\n			\n				Share on Bluesky (Opens in new window)\n				Bluesky\n			\n				Share on LinkedIn (Opens in new window)\n				LinkedIn\n			\n				Share on Threads (Opens in new window)\n				Threads\n			\n				Share on Nextdoor (Opens in new window)\n				Nextdoor\n			\n				Share on WhatsApp (Opens in new window)\n				WhatsApp\n			\n				Email a link to a friend (Opens in new window)\n				Email
URL:https://montclairlocal.news/event/open-book-open-mind-nicholas-lemann-returning/
LOCATION:Montclair Public Library\, 50 S Fullerton Ave\, Montclair\, NJ\, 07042\, United States
CATEGORIES:Art & Culture
